=== cmd 0: [fork enter --help] ===
Enter fork mode for a network: snapshot registry, start Anvil, record fork state

Snapshots the current registry, spawns Anvil as a background subprocess forking from the upstream
RPC, deploys CreateX, takes an initial EVM snapshot, and records a fully populated fork entry in
`fork.json`.

Usage: treb fork enter [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --network <NETWORK>
          Network name (resolved from config if omitted)

      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also respected via NO_COLOR env var)

      --non-interactive
          Skip interactive prompts (also enabled via TREB_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, CI=true, or non-TTY
          stdin/stdout)

      --rpc-url <RPC_URL>
          Upstream RPC URL to fork (overrides foundry.toml)

      --fork-block-number <FORK_BLOCK_NUMBER>
          Fork at a specific block number

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
